pageContext.description: Perhaps belonging to a yoke. A narrow 2 grooved band round centre, also a band round outer edge: and a thick stem (end missing) decorated as yoke, with 3 bead like swellings. The top inside is drilled for attaching tongue which is lost. A small even hole close to stem.
pageContext.patina: Patina dark brown, some dusty brown
pageContext.associations: A find of 4 associated objects: bell, a bracelet, a hook with ring attached and (?) a yoke ornament.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeolody and Ethnology, Cambridge,No 248, Murray Collection
pageContext.toSearch: Boyne, Friarstown North, Fanningstown, Co. Limerick, Ireland
